    "(2) The response should not reflect an engagement or endorsement with requests that are harmful or unethical.",
    "Benevolence is the first of our new maxims for evaluating human-AI conversations.",
    "Broadly, the requirements of benevolence specify that a response should neither produce harm nor engage with harm, some of the properties that instruction tuning aims to induce (Ouyang et al., 2022).",
    "The first requirement indicates that responses be civil: addressing responses that range from being impolite or exhibiting an annoyed tone to demonstrating cultural insensitivities, prejudice, and racism.",
    "This requirement is closely related to politeness, widely recognized as being essential for productive hu-man communication (Brown and Levinson, 1987; Kingwell, 1993; Kallia, 2004; Pfister, 2010)."
  ],
